OL,3,CStarmer under pressure to agree exit
OL,4,Cplan after election losses
OL,6,FSir Keir Starmer has vowed to listen
OL,7,Fto voters but refused to shift "left
OL,8,For right" despite pressure to change
OL,9,Fcourse and backbench calls for a new
OL,10,Fleader following Labour's electoral
OL,11,Fmauling.
OL,13,FThe Prime Minister said responding to
OL,14,F"tough" results, which saw Labour lose
OL,15,Fhundreds of councillors in England and
OL,16,Fsuffer humiliation in Wales, would
OL,17,Fmean "being assertive in our values"
OL,18,Fand "unifying rather than dividing".
OL,26,@oD@`OUpD@IO]vD@AOUvD@GO]yD@FOUyD@dO]zD@
OL,26,AEOUzD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778351320
OL,3,CStarmer under pressure to agree exit
OL,4,Cplan after election losses
OL,6,FThe ruling party haemorrhaged support
OL,7,Fin former strongholds while Reform UK
OL,8,Fmade stunning gains and Plaid Cymru
OL,9,Fbecame the largest party in a Senedd
OL,10,Felection that left outgoing First
OL,11,FMinister Eluned Morgan without a seat.
OL,13,FBut Labour MPs continued to question
OL,14,Fhis position and deputy leader Lucy
OL,15,FPowell said unless the party can win
OL,16,Fback voters lost to Reform UK and the
OL,17,FGreens then Nigel Farage would take
OL,18,Fthe keys to No 10 at the next general
OL,19,Felection.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778351320
OL,3,CStarmer under pressure to agree exit
OL,4,Cplan after election losses
OL,6,FThe Prime Minister will seek to use a
OL,7,Fmajor speech on Monday and then the
OL,8,FKing's Speech on Wednesday to attempt
OL,9,Fto reset his premiership in the
OL,10,Faftermath of the electoral mauling.
OL,12,FSir Keir has been caught by the rise
OL,13,Fof Reform UK on the right, with Mr
OL,14,FFarage's party making spectacular
OL,15,Fgains, and the Green Party on the left
OL,16,Falso making inroads in Labour's urban
OL,17,Fheartlands.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778351320
OL,3,CStarmer under pressure to agree exit
OL,4,Cplan after election losses
OL,6,FBut in a defiant op-ed for the
OL,7,FGuardian, the Prime Minister wrote:
OL,8,F"While we must respond to the message
OL,9,Fthat voters have sent us, that doesn't
OL,10,Fmean tacking right or left.
OL,12,F"It means bringing together a broad
OL,13,Fpolitical movement, being assertive
OL,14,Fabout our values, bold in our vision
OL,15,Fand addressing people's demands.
OL,17,F"Unifying rather than dividing. That
OL,18,Fis the right approach for our party
OL,19,Fand, more importantly, it is the right
OL,20,Fapproach for our country."
OL,26,@pD@AOUtD@AOUyD@AOU|D@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778351320
OL,3,CStarmer under pressure to agree exit
OL,4,Cplan after election losses
OL,6,FHe said concerns expressed among
OL,7,Fdifferent communities have "more in
OL,8,Fcommon than some would like to admit,"
OL,9,Fwith the cost of living uniting voters
OL,10,Facross the board.
OL,12,F"Our job is to convince them that we
OL,13,Fhave progressive answers to the
OL,14,Fproblems and challenges that they
OL,15,Fface," Sir Keir said.
OL,17,FLabour also suffered from voters
OL,18,Fswitching to the Green Party as Zack
OL,19,FPolanski said the era of two-party
OL,20,Fpolitics "is not just dying, it is
OL,21,Fdead and it is buried".
OL,26,@oD@\OUpD@fO]tD@AOUwD@FO]|D@JOU}D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778351320
OL,3,CStarmer under pressure to agree exit
OL,4,Cplan after election losses
OL,6,FFormer Cabinet minister Louise Haigh
OL,7,Ftold ITV Calendar: "I think what is
OL,8,Fabundantly clear is that unless the
OL,9,FGovernment delivers significant and
OL,10,Furgent change, then the Prime Minister
OL,11,Fcannot lead us into another election."
OL,13,FRichard Burgon, leader of the
OL,14,FSocialist Campaign Group of left-wing
OL,15,FLabour MPs, demanded Sir Keir set out
OL,16,Fa timetable for his departure.
OL,18,F"It is clear that Keir has fought his
OL,19,Flast election as Labour leader and,
OL,20,Fdeep down, he will know it," he said.
OL,26,@oD@TOUsD@fO]zD@AOU|D@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
